INTERNATIONAL FORCE 
The "U.N. Navy" (Aug.17) article was so right. The United States alone mustn't 
be enforcing international sanctions, but instead help to create a U.N. Naval 
Force to share the great cost and responsibility of the Persian Gulf crisis. 
Let's bring this to the attention of both President Bush and Secretary General 
Xavier Perez de Cuellar. 
LOYAL NICHOLS 
Newport Beach 
